def pie_plot(data, var_select, target) :
    S = data[data[target]==1]
    D = data[data[target]==0]
    
    col =['Silver', 'gold','#CF5C36','lightblue','magenta', '#FF5D73','#F2D7EE','mediumturquoise']
    
    trace1 = go.Pie(values  = D[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
                    labels  = D[var_select].value_counts().keys().tolist(),
                    textfont=dict(size=15), opacity = 0.8,
                    hole = 0.5, 
                    hoverinfo = "label+percent+name",
                    domain  = dict(x = [.0,.48]),
                    name    = "Active",
                    marker  = dict(colors = col, line = dict(width = 1.5)))
    trace2 = go.Pie(values  = S[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
                    labels  = S[var_select].value_counts().keys().tolist(),
                    textfont=dict(size=15), opacity = 0.8,
                    hole = 0.5,
                    hoverinfo = "label+percent+name",
                    marker  = dict(line = dict(width = 1.5)),
                    domain  = dict(x = [.52,1]),
                    name    = "Losing" )

    layout = go.Layout( dict(title = var_select + " distribution by target ",
                            annotations = [ dict(text = "Active"+" : "+"549",
                                                font = dict(size = 13),
                                                showarrow = False,
                                                x = .22, y = -0.1),
                                            dict(text = "Losing"+" : "+"342",
                                                font = dict(size = 13),
                                                showarrow = False,
                                                x = .8,y = -.1)]),
                       barmode='stack',)
                                          

    fig  = go.Figure(data = [trace1,trace2],layout = layout)
    py.iplot(fig)



def barplot(data, var_select , title, target, log:str='-') :
    S = data[data[target]==1]
    D = data[data[target]==0]
    tmp1 = S
    tmp2 = D

    color=['lightskyblue','gold']
    trace2 = go.Bar(
        x=tmp1[var_select].value_counts().keys().tolist(),
        y=tmp1[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
        text=tmp1[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
        textposition = 'auto',
        name='Losing',opacity = 1, marker=dict(
        color='lightskyblue',
        line=dict(color='#000000',width=1)))

    trace1 = go.Bar(
        x=tmp2[var_select].value_counts().keys().tolist(),
        y=tmp2[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
        text=tmp2[var_select].value_counts().values.tolist(),
        textposition = 'auto',
        name='Active', opacity = 1, marker=dict(
        color='pink',
        line=dict(color='#000000',width=1)))

    layout = dict(title = title,
                  autosize = True,
                  height  = 500,
                  width   = 830,
                  #barmode = 'stack',
                  xaxis=dict(), 
                  yaxis=dict(title= 'Count', type=log),
                 legend=dict(x=-.1, y=1.5))

    fig = go.Figure(data=[trace1, trace2], layout=layout)
    py.iplot(fig)
    
    
# Defining missing plot to detect all missing values in dataset
def missing_plot(dataset, key) :
    null_feat = pd.DataFrame(len(dataset[key]) - dataset.isnull().sum(), columns = ['Count'])
    percentage_null = pd.DataFrame((len(dataset[key]) - (len(dataset[key]) - dataset.isnull().sum()))/len(dataset[key])*100,\
                                   columns = ['Count'])
    percentage_null = percentage_null.round(2)

    trace = go.Bar(x = null_feat.index, y = null_feat['Count'] ,opacity = 0.8, text = percentage_null['Count'],  \
                   textposition = 'auto',marker=dict(color = 'lightblue',\
            line=dict(color='#000000',width=1.5)))

    layout = dict(title= "Missing Values (count & %)")

    fig = dict(data = [trace], layout=layout)
    py.iplot(fig)

# totally per 4 months        
dataset['sum_turnover'] = 0
dataset['sum_qty'] = 0
for month in [2, 3, 4, 5]:
        dataset.sum_turnover += dataset['last{0}_turn_all'.format(month)]
        dataset.sum_qty += dataset['last{0}_qty'.format(month)]   
        

# absolute per each month-change
for month in [2, 3, 4]:
    dataset['turnover_abs_{0}_decrease'.format(month)] = \
                    ((dataset['last{0}_turn_all'.format(month)]/dataset['sum_turnover']) * 100) - ((dataset['last{0}_turn_all'.format(month + 1)]/dataset['sum_turnover']) * 100)
    dataset['qty_abs_{0}_decrease'.format(month)] = \
                    ((dataset['last{0}_qty'.format(month)]/dataset['sum_qty']) * 100) - ((dataset['last{0}_qty'.format(month + 1)]/dataset['sum_qty']) * 100)
    
# percentage trend
dataset['perc_trend'] = dataset.qty_abs_4_decrease + dataset.qty_abs_3_decrease + dataset.qty_abs_2_decrease
